review_ru: I stayed in Faynyy during my trip to Carpathian Mountains. Located near major ski resort (Bukovel), river Prut, 45 ft waterfall Hook, and Chornogirski National Park with the highest mountain in Ukraine Hoverla (6,630 ft) this family run hotel is a real find. Lodge-style, all- wood spacious rooms, with great ameneties and excellent ethnic (hucul) cuisine. I highly recommend you to find this place and spend a night or several. You will have plenty to do in the area, and you would appreaciate your cozy room.  If you are worried about price, you would be pleasantly surprised!!! Super affordable!
